content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure appears to be a small house or church-like building
- It has 3 distinct layers
- Features a central archway in red at the bottom
- Has green blocks as the base and sides
- Contains a blue block on the upper level
- Orange/red triangular pieces form the roof
- Total number of blocks used: approximately 8-9 blocks

Layer-by-layer breakdown:
Bottom layer: Green rectangular blocks with a red arch in the center
Middle layer: Green and blue blocks forming walls
Top layer: Orange/red triangular blocks forming a peaked roof

Required blocks from dictionary and assembly order:

{
Step1: Move block with index 9 (Green horizontal base block)
Step2: Move block with index 11 (Green horizontal base block)
Step3: Move block with index 1 (Red arch block)
Step4: Move block with index 10 (Green vertical block for left wall)
Step5: Move block with index 7 (Blue cube for right wall)
Step6: Move block with index 15 (Orange triangular block for left roof)
Step7: Move block with index 14 (Orange triangular block for center roof)
Step8: Move block with index 16 (Orange triangular block for right roof)
}

This assembly sequence builds the structure from bottom to top, ensuring stability and proper alignment of all pieces.
